						               													<description>Permutu is a pure abstract strategy game with random setup. The goal is to collect sets of tiles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 78 tiles, each with one of 26 symbols and one of 3 colors. Each symbol appears on 3 tiles, in 3 different colors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During setup, 3 parallel rows of tiles are randomly laid out, one row for each color, creating columns with 1 tile of each color.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During play, players will take tiles, taking turns in clockwise order.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can take a single tile from a column with 3 tiles, if no one (including you) already has a tile with that tile's symbol.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can take an entire column (of 3 or fewer tiles), if you have tiles which match the symbols on all of that column's tiles, or all but one of its tiles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you have no move, pass.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once everyone has no move, the game is over.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Score 3 points for each triple collected with the same symbol, and 1 point for each pair collected with the same symbol.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
